-------------------------
MACTRONIX  MX83C305/6
-------------------------

Filename   Port      Description  MX83C305/6 chipset with built-in 8K cache
--------   -------   ---------------------------------------------------------
V062B300   MXIC300   "Dual 386" chipset, MX83C305/6
V062B302   MXIC302   x062B300 (T-)
V062B303   MXIC303   x062B300 (T+)   <-- demo board
V062B304   MXIC304   x062B300 (TL-)
V062B305   MXIC305   x062B300 (TL+)


Filename   Port      Description  MX83C305/6,  Port92,  Cyrix design-in
--------   -------   ---------------------------------------------------------
V062B308   MXIC308   "Dual 386" chipset, MX83C305/6
V062B30A   MXIC30A   x062B308 (T-)
V062B30B   MXIC30B   x062B308 (T+)   <-- demo board
V062B30C   MXIC30C   x062B308 (TL-)
V062B30D   MXIC30D   x062B308 (TL+)

NOTE!!  Versions '308-30D  *CANNOT*  be used with 1st pass silicon.

        When new 0.8u silicon is available, the Port92 (PS2 FAST_A20)
        feature will be available.  The earlier 1.0u silicon does not
        support Port92 PS2 style FAST_A20.  These bios' will crash!

NOTE!!  Versions '308-30D require Cyrix layout with #A20M and #FLUSH.
        (If Cyrix CPU is not used, it doesn't matter).

        Please confirm with MACTRONIX that your layout will operate
        correctly with Port92-FAST_A20 usage and Cyrix #A20M pin enabled.
        Otherwise, use the '300-305 bios versions.


------------------------------------------------------------------------------

-----------------------------------------------------------------
 8042 Turbo/Turbo-LED control:  (T-) (T+) (TL-) (TL+) (CL-) (CL+)
-----------------------------------------------------------------

Hot-Key TURBO and/or LED control via keystrokes  <CTRL> <ALT> <-/+>  will
simultaneously activate all commonly used 8042 pins: 23,24, 27,28,29,30.

The system board layout must connect one of these pins to an existing
Turbo/LED circuit.  Consideration should be given to the remaining pins
which are also driven.  MR BIOS (r) 8042 or AMI KF keyboard controller
may be used for this purpose.  Award, Phoenix, and Quadtel 8042's cannot
be used with any MR BIOS (r) version designated as having this special
8042 functionality.

                  Active
Legend  Function  State   Description
------  --------  -----   -------------------------------------------- 
(T-)    Turbo      Low    8042 turbo/LED circuit ONLY (no chipset register
(T+)    Turbo      High   turbo).  Also, Setup Utility SPEED screen appears.

(TL-)   Turbo-LED  Low    Both chipset turbo and 8042 pins are activated.
(TL+)   Turbo-LED  High

(CL-)   Cache-LED  Low    Used mainly with 486, Cache state indicates "turbo".
(CL+)   Cache-LED  High

